      "widgets_values": [
        "**htdemucs_ft** — best for vocals. Fine-tuned version of htdemucs with extra training specifically on each stem. Slower but noticeably cleaner separation, especially on vocals.\n\n**htdemucs** — the base Hybrid Transformer Demucs model. Fast, good quality, solid all-rounder. Use this if speed matters more than perfection.\n\n**mdx_extra** — MDX architecture (different from Hybrid Transformer). Trained on extra data. Competitive with htdemucs_ft on vocals, sometimes better on certain music styles. Worth trying if htdemucs_ft leaves artifacts.\n\n**mdx_extra_q** — quantized version of mdx_extra. Smaller, faster, slightly lower quality. Use only if VRAM is tight.\n\n**For vocal separation:** start with `htdemucs_ft`. If you hear bleed or artifacts, try `mdx_extra` as a second opinion — they make different kinds of mistakes so one may work better depending on the track.\n\nThe `shifts` widget also matters a lot for vocal quality — default is 1, but setting it to 4 or higher significantly reduces artifacts at the cost of being proportionally slower."
      ],
